          <div class="text-body-light space-y-3">
            <p>Modern plumbing isn’t just about convenience—it’s also about sustainability. Eco-friendly plumbing solutions can help you save water, lower utility bills, and reduce your environmental impact. Consider installing low-flow toilets, faucets, and showerheads to significantly cut water usage without sacrificing performance.</p>
            <p>Tankless water heaters are another great option, providing hot water on demand and using less energy than traditional tanks. Fixing leaks promptly and upgrading to energy-efficient appliances can further boost your home’s eco-credentials.</p>
            <p>Ask your plumber about greywater systems and rainwater harvesting for irrigation. These solutions not only conserve water but also promote a greener, more sustainable lifestyle for your family or business.</p>
          </div>
