        <div class="p-6 flex flex-col flex-1">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-2 text-heading-light">5 Signs You Need a Professional Plumber</h3>
          <div class="text-body-light space-y-3">
            <p>Some plumbing issues can be handled with a DIY approach, but others require the expertise of a professional. Persistent low water pressure, recurring clogs, or slow drains often indicate deeper problems in your plumbing system.</p>
            <p>Unusual noises like banging or gurgling pipes, water stains on walls or ceilings, and unexplained increases in your water bill are all red flags. If you notice foul odors coming from your drains or see visible signs of mold, it’s time to call a licensed plumber.</p>
            <p>Addressing these issues early can prevent costly damage and ensure your plumbing system remains safe and efficient. Don’t hesitate to seek professional help when in doubt!</p>
